---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import NewsletterFooter from '../components/NewsletterFooter.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Speaking" description="Tomomi Sasaki speaks about design research, design sprints and workshop facilitation." canonicalUrl="https://www.ripplet.org/speaking">
  <Header currentPath="/speaking" />
  <main>
    <div class="page-content">
      <h1>Speaking</h1>
      <p>I speak about the wild and wonderful challenges of applying design skills to complex challenges, with a focus on design research, design sprints and workshop facilitation.</p>
      <p>Public speaking is externalizing what I've learned and contributing to a bigger discussion about how to create more impact through our work. My biggest stage so far was the global Interaction conference hosted by IxDA. The smallest was a meetup at my studio office. Both were great fun.</p>
      <p>If you're interested in having me speak at your event, <a href="/contact">get in touch.</a></p>

      <h2>Recorded talks</h2>
      <div class="video-grid">
        <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dv-VWnmbEZ0" title="Intersection 23: innovation portfolio management" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture"></iframe>
        <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/M-e3sIq91GE" title="Agile Tampere 2022: Work at Any Time" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture"></iframe>
        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/472541836" title="Namahn Lectures: Learning as a social practice" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen"></iframe>
        <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/owIFeITO7O8" title="Intersection 19: Eurotunnel customer experience case study" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture"></iframe>
      </div>

      <h2>Podcast interviews</h2>
      <ul class="collection-list">
        <li><a href="https://theconversationfactory.com/podcast/facilitation-and-self-leadership" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Facilitation and Self Leadership"</a> on the Conversation Factory, hosted by Daniel Stillman</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.buzzsprout.com/1987327/11010960-ep-07-distributed-teams-and-its-impact-on-collaboration-with-tomomi-sasaki-from-aq" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Distributed Teams and Its Impact on Collaboration"</a> on LeanCast: Product Innovation &amp; UX Design</li>
        <li><a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/7AxOhZcPthf6nlnp4mqX1G" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Emotions at Work"</a> on Greaterthan's The How, hosted by Alícia Trepat Pont in the series Affectively</li>
        <li><a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/251FQoJvPFnqRyIKGMNhxD" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"The Emotional Lens of Collaboration"</a> on Greaterthan's The How, hosted by Alícia Trepat Pont in Affectively</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Speaking history</h2>
      <div class="speaking-history">
      <p><a href="https://www.bloomworld.org/midwifing-change-summit"><strong>Midwifing Change Summit</strong></a><br>In Nov 2025, I joined a fishbowl discussion with Greaterthan colleagues about exploring postgrowth principles &amp; money.</p>
      <p><a href="https://irmuk.co.uk/sdc-2024/"><strong>Service Design Conference Europe</strong></a><br>In April 2024 in London, I gave a talk with Milan Guenther about our project with the OECD.</p>
      <p><a href="https://intersection.group/events/intersection23-oecd"><strong>Creating sustainable global impact in international development organisations</strong></a><br>In September 2023, I gave a case study talk with Angela Hanson from the OECD at the Intersection Conference.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-anatomy-of-an-engaging-workshop-tickets-620089613727"><strong>The Anatomy of an Engaging Workshop</strong></a><br>In July 2023, I delivered a 2hr online workshop with Women Talk Design.</p>
      <p><a href="https://opencollective.com/foundation/events/collaborative-funding-w-cobudget-a5ea9c23"><strong>Collaborative Funding with Cobudget</strong></a><br>In December 2022, I gave a 2hr training session with David Weingartner for the Open Collective Foundation. <a href="https://opencollective.com/foundation/events/collaborative-funding-w-cobudget-a5ea9c23">Recording and slides available.</a></p>
      <p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/tomomi-sasaki-learning-as-a-social-activity-tickets-404890748127"><strong>Learning as a social practice</strong></a><br>In November 2022, I joined Dr Leigh George in an online conversation as part of Freedom Anniversary Conversations.</p>
      <p><strong>The Human Experience of Facilitating Co-design and Dialog</strong><br>In October 2022, I gave a keynote talk and participated in a panel discussion at Design Thinking Tallinn.</p>
      <p><strong>Work from Anywhere. Work Anytime.</strong><br>In September 2022, I gave a talk with Andrea Darabos on how teams can create more focus and flow, for the <a href="https://agiletampere.fi">Agile Tampere</a> conference.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/turn-your-talk-into-a-workshop-tickets-323322254567"><strong>Turn your talk into a workshop</strong></a><br>In May 2022, I delivered a 2hr online workshop with Women Talk Design. Repeated Jan 2023.</p>
      <p><a href="https://namahn.com/lectures/tomomi-sasaki/"><strong>Learning as a social practice: ideas to increase our range for growth</strong></a><br>In October 2020, I delivered this new talk as a webinar hosted by Namahn's Lectures. <a href="https://namahn.com/lectures/tomomi-sasaki/">Recording and slides</a> available.</p>
      <p><strong>Using the Research Skills Framework</strong> (with Dave Hora)<br>
        In April 2020, for the <a href="https://www.meetup.com/ResearchOps-Berlin/events/270235620/">ResearchOps Berlin community</a> [online]<br>
        In May 2020, for the <a href="https://www.meetup.com/Design-at-Scale-Barcelona/events/270463350/">Design at Scale Barcelona/Madrid</a> community [online]<br>
        In September 2020, for <a href="https://uxinsight.org/festival/">UXInsight Festival 2020</a> [online]
      </p>
      <p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com.au/e/launch-event-the-research-skills-framework-tickets-99716392414"><strong>ResearchOps Community Town Hall</strong></a><br>In March 2020, I organized a community Town Hall to celebrate the launch of the Research Skills Framework with Dave Hora. <a href="https://vimeo.com/44524294">Recording</a> available.</p>
      <p><a href="https://interaction20.ixda.org/"><strong>IxDA Interaction 20</strong></a><br>In February 2020 in Milan, I gave a talk about the <a href="https://github.com/researchops/researcherskills-workshop/">Researcher Skills Framework</a> with <a href="https://www.davesresearch.com/">Dave Hora</a>. <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1luDPI-6J4i-qLMoKTSvF_Z4Jc8sPHGVL">Slides</a> available.</p>
      <p><strong>Intro to Research Operations</strong><br>In January 2020, I led a 2hr event about Research Operations for Design Research Tokyo. <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1WmcOGiXagDec-orTO8OAPqrwnEtUnx_d/view?usp=sharing">Slides</a> available [Japanese].</p>
      <p><a href="https://designsprintkit.withgoogle.com/conference-2019/home"><strong>Google Design Sprint Conference</strong></a><br>In October 2019 in Boulder, Colorado I ran a deep dive session with Milan Guenther about enterprise design sprints. <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=182t5Zc2KCe2aId46a4FiIhQ5ytBj_WlY">Slides</a> and <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=10blrRl3ptoPAPQTvgVfN4EhMVlXvue_A">material</a> available.</p>
      <p><a href="https://2019.intersectionconf.com/"><strong>Intersection 19</strong></a><br>In September 2019 in Lisbon, I presented <a href="https://2019.intersectionconf.com/sessions/building-bridges-together.php">a customer experience case study</a> with <a href="https://twitter.com/Mael_I">Mael Inizan</a>. <a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1UPGRSxK5Dllk5l_ElyjVyDXpD0dynyCq-LoV5R_Dm-s/edit?usp=sharing">Slides</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=owIFeITO7O8">recording</a> available.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.meetup.com/Write-the-Docs-Paris/events/260964602/"><strong>Inaugural event for Write The Docs Paris chapter</strong></a><br>I shared three stories from my experience in corporate Japan that shaped my understanding of the act of documentation.</p>
      <p><a href="https://www.lelaptop.com/evenement/google-sprint-conference/"><strong>Google Design Sprint Conference — Paris</strong></a><br>In April 2019, I gave a talk about "Orchestrating multiple design sprints". <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1IwCy8oYCFmchLyuqI48pYspwn9ByRskq/view">Slides</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4NXdHGePnX4">recording</a> available.</p>
      <p><strong>World Information Architecture Day 2019</strong><br>In February 2019 during the <a href="https://www.worldiaday.org/events/hong-kong/2019">Hong Kong edition</a> of WIAD, I gave an introductory workshop about design sprints under the global theme 'design for difference'.</p>
      <p><strong>Research as an organizational capability</strong><br>In January 2019 at a Design Research Tokyo event about scaling research. I curated and hosted this event, and delivered one of the talks. <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=19f0L5wLLcYporGVbqEcsN99S0A7oVVqc">Slides</a> available [Japanese].</p>
      <p><strong>Women Talk Design — Design Your Talk Topic workshop</strong><br>
        In December 2018 at <a href="https://ridethelightning.doorkeeper.jp/events/84191">Ride the Lightning</a> in Tokyo<br>
        In January 2019 at <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/design-your-talk-topic-singapore-tickets-53943753218">GovTech</a> in Singapore with <a href="https://twitter.com/duzkiez">Sam Yuen</a><br>
        In June 2019 in Paris with the <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/hexagon-ux-paris-workshop-design-your-talk-topic-tickets-62883843268">Hexagon UX community</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>Design sprints and cross-cultural innovation</strong><br>In October 2018 at Google's <a href="https://designsprintkit.withgoogle.com/conference-2018">Design Sprint Conference</a> in San Francisco.</p>
      <p><strong>Design Meets Improv workshop</strong><br>I led a half-day workshop for the <a href="http://appliedimprovisation.network/events/2018-paris/">Applied Improvisation Network Conference 2018</a> with <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/asimonson/">Alexandre Simon</a> and Bård Brænde.</p>
      <p><strong>Delivering more impact through UX research</strong><br>In April 2018 at <a href="https://www.meetup.com/Umami-Design-Talks/events/248917013/">Umami Talk</a> in Brussels, Belgium.</p>
      <p><strong>Design to Ignite — Design sprints for transformation at scale</strong> (with Milan Guenther)<br>
        In February 2018 at <a href="https://interaction18.ixda.org/program/talk-design-to-ignite--design-sprints-for-transformation-at-scale-sasaki-tomomi-milan-guenther/">IxDA Interaction 18</a> in Lyon, France<br>
        In March 2018 at <a href="https://irmuk.co.uk/agendas/innovation-business-change-and-transformation-conference-europe/">Innovation, Business Change and Transformation Conference Europe 2018</a> in London<br>
        In April 2018 at IxDA Oslo in Oslo, Norway
      </p>
      <p><strong>Working across cultures, and the role that intercultural exchange plays in innovation</strong><br>In November 2017 at <a href="https://connpass.com/event/87940/">Intercultural Innovation Meetup</a> in Lille, France.</p>
      <p><strong>Design Sprints at Scale</strong><br>
        In July 2017 for <a href="https://www.eventbrite.fr/e/billets-ux-paris-ixda-paris-design-sprints-at-scale-par-tomomi-sasaki-35455769160">UX Paris / IxDA Paris</a><br>
        A salon version in Summer 2017 for <a href="https://ridethelightning.doorkeeper.jp/">Ride the Lightning</a> in Tokyo<br>
        In November 2017 for <a href="http://2017.leankanban.fr/sessions/design-sprint-at-scale/">Lean Kanban France</a>
      </p>
      <p><strong>What we talk about when we talk about chatbots at AQ</strong><br>In July 2016 for <a href="https://ridethelightning.doorkeeper.jp/events/48860">Ride the Lightning</a> in Tokyo.</p>
      <p><strong>User research as a team sport</strong><br><a href="http://www.intrapreneurshipconference.com/speaker/tomomi-sasaki/">Intrapreneurship Conference 2016</a> organized by NUMA in Paris.</p>
      <p><strong>Let's talk about users — why do qualitative research</strong><br><a href="https://coe.qualiware.com/2nd-enterprise-design-retreat/">2016 Enterprise Design Retreat</a> in Iceland.</p>
      <p><strong>On distributed teams, multilingual collaboration and the power of facilitation</strong><br>2016 <a href="http://uxmilk.jp/8984">UX Jam</a> in Tokyo.</p>
      <p><strong>Anatomy of a workshop: how to design, prepare for and facilitate workshops</strong><br>2016, self-organized event at <a href="http://lelaptop.com">Laptop</a> in Paris.</p>
      <p><strong>Content strategy for digital practitioners</strong><br>SwapSkills #05 in Tokyo.</p>
      <p><strong>Designing the museum coupon app MuPon</strong><br><a href="https://www.museumnext.com/museumnext-barcelona-2012/">MuseumNext 2012</a> in Barcelona, Spain. <a href="https://vimeo.com/44524294">Recording</a> available.</p>
      <p><strong>Designing the onboarding experience</strong><br><a href="http://www.uxcampeurope.org/">UXcamp Europe 2012</a> in Berlin, Germany.</p>
      </div>
      <NewsletterFooter />
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    max-width: 960px;
  }

  .video-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .video-grid iframe {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .video-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .collection-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0 !important;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .collection-list li::before { display: none !important; }

  .collection-list li {
    padding: 6px 0;
    margin: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .speaking-history p {
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
</style>
